 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Feral (Cat) Druid Phase 1 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 334 top-ranked Feral (Cat) Druid DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 1 (Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Feral (Cat) Druid items in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Wolfshead Helm (95%), Everbloom Idol (95%), Terestian's Stranglestaff (85%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Feral (Cat) Druid use in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Delicate Living Ruby and Glinting Noble Topaz in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Feral (Cat) Druid need in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Might of the Scourge on shoulders and Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
  }
 ]
